---
title: "Ergative marker type"
author: "Asya Alekseeva"
date: 2025-08-28
format: html
css: styles.css
---



We classified the variants of the ergative marker into r-type (e.g. *balʁu-ra* [fish.OBL-ERG]) and non-r-type (e.g. *gagaj-e* [uncle-ERG], *gagaj-Ø* [uncle-ERG]). We elicited four nouns in the singular and in the plural: ‘uncle’ (SG) and ‘uncle’ (PL) (animate, human), ‘fish’ (SG) and ‘fish’ (PL) (animate, non-human), ‘river’ (SG) and ‘rock’ (PL) (inanimate, non-human). The elicited contexts were as follows: ‘(My) uncle helped me to build a house’, ‘(My) uncles helped me to build a house’, ‘The fish (SG) ate the fly’, ‘The fish (PL) ate the flies’, ‘The river demolished the bridge’, ‘The rocks broke the roof’. The maps show the type (r-type or non-r-type) of the ergative marker used in each of the contexts, respectively.


